{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","level":2},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-404-Debugging-with-Xcode-9","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-407-Understanding-Undefined-Behavior","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-709-Advances-in-Networking-Part-2"]}],"kind":"content"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/238\/","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Read Transcript"}},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-238-Writing-Energy-Efficient-Apps","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Writing Energy Efficient Apps","roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-238-writing-energy-efficient-apps"]}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"People expect long battery life on their mobile devices, and apps play a vital role in achieving that experience. Learn strategies to conserve energy while providing the best experience for your app. Find out about the key areas that affect energy consumption of an app as well as how to best use the available APIs to optimize battery life. Master energy debugging tools to make your app more energy efficient."}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-709-Advances-in-Networking-Part-2":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-709-Advances-in-Networking-Part-2","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about important improvements to URLSession. Find out how to use new URLSession APIs to better handle connectivity fluctuations, to schedule background session tasks, and to receive progress reports for session tasks. Plus, gain insights into valuable best practices, tips, and news about ongoing work with emerging network technologies."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Advances in Networking, Part 2","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-709-advances-in-networking-part-2"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-407-Understanding-Undefined-Behavior":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-407-Understanding-Undefined-Behavior","title":"Understanding Undefined Behavior","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Undefined behavior in programming languages can introduce difficult to diagnose bugs and even lead to security vulnerabilities in your App. Learn more about undefined behavior, the tools available in Xcode 9 that address it, and why Swift is safer by design.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-407-understanding-undefined-behavior","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-404-Debugging-with-Xcode-9":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9 introduces wireless development for iOS and tvOS. Discover how to configure and use wireless development with your devices. Learn about Xcode’s latest debugging features — including debugging workflow enhancements, and new view debugging support for view controllers, SpriteKit and SceneKit — now with no strings attached."}],"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-404-debugging-with-xcode-9","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Debugging with Xcode 9","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-404-Debugging-with-Xcode-9"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","type":"image"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","type":"link"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/238/":{"checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/238\/","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/w